Vice President Kamala Harris addressed the issue of voting rights in America during a visit to Detroit, Michigan. She commended the legislators in Texas who are standing up for the rights of all Americans to vote. Harris believes that fighting for the right to vote is fundamental to democracy. She also highlighted the importance of voting by mentioning the outcomes that Michigan voters achieved in the 2020 election, such as a national plan for vaccinations, more jobs, and an expanded Child Tax Credit. Harris emphasized the need to ensure that all Americans can express their voice through the ballot and their vote. She thanked the leaders on the ground for their work in making these rights a reality and expressed her commitment to the cause.